In Fixture Monkey Container means data structures including Collection. ex. Map, Optional, Set, List&hellip;
user-defined data structures are also considered as a Container
This practice deals with manipulation size. 0. Class # public class Generate { List&lt;GenerateElement&gt; values; } public class GenerateElement { List&lt;String&gt; values; } 1. Generating ArbitraryBuilder # ArbitraryBuilder&lt;Generate&gt; generateBuilder = fixtureMonkey.giveMeBuilder(Generate.class); 2-1. Alter field size # general expression Kotlin Exp generateBuilder.size(&#34;values&#34;, 5); generateBuilder.sizeExp(Generate::values, 5); 2-2. Alter field n-th element size # general expression Kotlin Exp generateBuilder.
